result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Dylan Thomas Rauman not in court, in custody.  Attorney Jason A Findling in court for Dylan Thomas Rauman.  Attorney Dennis Patrick Murphy in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for a scheduling conference. Defense has discovery, but has not received an offer. State will convey an offer to defense. Defense requests a status date. Court grants request. Case remains calendared in Branch 11.
Status conference scheduled for November 9, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Dylan Thomas Rauman in court by video with Attorney Jason A Findling who appears in person.  Defendant Dylan Thomas Rauman in custody.  Abby Rockendorf appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: Greenfield Officer L. Dziedzic.  State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 11.  Scheduling conference scheduled for September 30, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Received and Filed: Attorney Jason Findling
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with Coldspring Liquor; BR.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Dylan Thomas Rauman in court with attorney Stephen Andrew Sargent.  Defendant Dylan Thomas Rauman in custody.  Michael J. Odden appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Dylan Thomas Rauman appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Swanson, Branch 11.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Commissioner advised DNA sample has been obtained from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant he may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if he meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4).  This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 16, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
